<TITLE> Jiban Bima gets automated </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 6 (bdnews24.com)Jiban Bima Corporation, the state-owned life insurer became automated Thursday as it launched an 'Online Insurance System'. Finance minister AMA Muhith launched the system, which JBC officials said aims to ensure transparency and access to information. The initiative includes a powerful storage system, multilevel security and a web based software. "Modernising always opens up windows of opportunities for an industry," he told the audience of the ceremony," Muhith said, at the Jiban Bima Bhaban launch. He hoped that the effort would lead the insurer to offer more products and services to the public. Bangladesh Bank governor Atiur Rahman, also present, said that ICT was the key to quality customer service. "It [ICT] has helped the world economy to gain pace and be more efficient." "Use of ICT is increasing rapidly in every realm of trade and commerce in today's world and Bangladesh is already late and can't afford further delay in this regard," added the central bank chief. Speaking as a special guest, the Securities and Exchange Commission's chairman Ziaul Haque Khandaker sought more participation from JBC in the capital market. "We hope Jiban Bima Corporation will come up with mutual funds." The launching ceremony also heard from JBC managing director Kaosar Zahura and JBC chairman Rafiqul Islam. "This is a big leap towards progress and the vision of a Digital Bangladesh," said Muhith, reaffirming the government's commitment to realising the vision within the next 12 years.
